                  <article class=3D"topic reference nested1" aria-labelledb=
y=3D"ariaid-title2" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"reference_hpf_bny_1cb">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title2">R=
equest Structure</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body refbody">
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_hpf_bny_=
1cb__d9597e248">
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Request Structure:</p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Requests are sent to the <span cl=
ass=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">management center</span></span> as HTTPS requ=
ests with the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) of the form described below=
:
                           </p>
                           <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>https://&lt;m=
anagement_center_IP_or_name&gt;:&lt;https_port&gt;/&lt;object_URL&gt;/objec=
t_UUID<em class=3D"ph i">options</em></code></pre>
                           <p class=3D"p">Where:</p>
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul" id=3D"reference_hpf_bny_1cb__ul=
_zv4_nmb_kw">
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>&lt;management_center_IP_or_name&gt;</code></pre> is the IP a=
ddress or Fully Qualified Domain Name of the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph">management center</span></span></section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>&lt;https_port&gt;</code></pre> is the port number used by th=
e <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">management center</span></span> for=
 HTTPS connections. This port is always 443.
                                 </section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>&lt;object_URL&gt;</code></pre> is the specific URL for the d=
esired resource. These URLs are unique for each resource and are given belo=
w.</section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code><em class=3D"ph i">options</em></code></pre> are the options =
given with the request. Options can be used to modify the output and filter=
 results. </section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code><em class=3D"ph i">{UUID}</em></code></pre> Many URLs contain=
 one or more UUIDs which must be specified. Most URIs include the domain UU=
ID, which can be found in the
                                    Authentication Token. When deleting or =
modifying an object, or requesting information about a specific object, the=
 URI will
                                    end with the object UUID.</section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                           </ul>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Available request methods are:</p=
>
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul" id=3D"reference_hpf_bny_1cb__ul=
_tpf_bny_1cb">
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>GET</code></pre> =E2=80=93 Retrieves data from the specified =
object. GET is a read-only operation. </section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>PUT</code></pre> =E2=80=93 Adds the supplied information to t=
he specified object; returns a 404 Resource Not Found error if the object d=
oes not exist.</section>
                                =20
                                 <table class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" rol=
e=3D"note">
                                    <tbody><tr>
                                       <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" =
role=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam=
/en/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                          <section class=3D"note__content">
                                             <hr>
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">Currently PUT m=
ay be used to create a new object, but this ability may be removed in later=
 releases. Use POST to create new
                                                objects and PUT to modify e=
xisting objects.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <hr>
                                          </section>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                 </tbody></table>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>POST</code></pre> =E2=80=93 Creates the object with the suppl=
ied information. POST operations should be followed with a payload consisti=
ng of the JSON
                                    object to be created, enclosed in brace=
s: <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>{object]</code></pre></section>
                                =20
                                 <table class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" rol=
e=3D"note">
                                    <tbody><tr>
                                       <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" =
role=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam=
/en/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                          <section class=3D"note__content">
                                             <hr>
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">The maximum num=
ber of rules you can use depends on memory of the device. There is no set l=
imit, because complex rules use
                                                more memory. For rule perfo=
rmance and optimization guidelines, see the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=
=3D"ph">management center</span></span> Configuration Guide.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <hr>
                                          </section>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                 </tbody></table>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>DELETE</code></pre> =E2=80=93 Deletes the specified object.</=
section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>PATCH</code></pre> =E2=80=93 <strong class=3D"ph b">Not suppo=
rted.</strong></section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                           </ul>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">The API supports query parameters=
 for almost all requests. For GET requests, the following query parameters =
can be used to
                              control the number of of returned objects and=
 the pagination:
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul" id=3D"reference_hpf_bny_1cb__ul=
_hfs_t1j_kw">
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>expanded</code></pre> - This is a True/False value which indi=
cates whether you get a full listing of an item in a list or only a referen=
ce. Some
                                    fields will only show if this flag is s=
et to true.</section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>offset</code></pre> - Indicates the position in the list wher=
e you want to start.</section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>limit</code></pre> - Indicates the number of items you want t=
o retrieve in a page.</section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                           </ul>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">The API supports filtering on the=
 basis of query parameters passed with a request. Filtering can be done bas=
ed on specific
                              attributes in a model. The parameters availab=
le for filtering vary by object, and are listed with the request below.
                           </p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic reference nested1" aria-labelledb=
y=3D"ariaid-title3" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"reference_frz_mmy_1cb">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title3">B=
ulk Rule Posting</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body refbody">
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_frz_mmy_=
1cb__section_wc4_4ll_wy">
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Multiple access control rules can=
 be added with a POST command using the bulk insert feature. This feature a=
llows as many
                              as 1,000 rules to be addded at once.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">This feature is only available fo=
r access rules.</p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">The URL for this feature is:</p>
                           <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>https://{fmc_=
IP_or_name}:{https_port}/api/fmc_config/v1/domain/{domain_UUID}/policy/acce=
sspolicies/{policy_UUID}/accessrules<em class=3D"ph i">?bulk=3Dtrue</em></c=
ode></pre>
                           <p class=3D"p">The option:</p>
                           <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>?bulk=3Dtrue<=
/code></pre>
                           <p class=3D"p">indicates that that multiple rule=
s will be used in the payload of this request.</p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">All objects in the payload of the=
 bulk POST request must be of the same type. You cannot mix different objec=
ts in the same
                              bulk request.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Unlike a normal POST operation, t=
he bulk POST requires a list of JSON objects. This list may have as many as=
 1,000 objects
                              or as few as one. The individual JSON objects=
 must be enclosed in braces. Each object must be separated by commas, and t=
he
                              entire list is enclosed in brackets:
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"p">
                              <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>[{object}]=
</code></pre>
                              <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>[{object1}=
,{object2},{object3},{object4},{object5} =E2=80=A6]</code></pre>
                              </section>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">The following query parameters ar=
e supported in bulk POST requests:</p>
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul" id=3D"reference_frz_mmy_1cb__ul=
_xc4_4ll_wy">
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>bulk=3D=
true</code></pre>
                                 <p class=3D"p">This parameter specifies th=
at the bulk POST feature is being used in the query. This parameter is <str=
ong class=3D"ph b">required</strong> for bulk rule posting.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>section=
=3Dmandatory/default</code></pre>
                                 <p class=3D"p">This parameter specifies th=
e section into which the rules will be added. If this parameter is not used=
 the section will be
                                    the default section. Only <code class=
=3D"ph codeph">mandatory</code> and <code class=3D"ph codeph">default</code=
> are allowed values. If a section is specified it must exist or the reques=
t will fail. If a section is specified, a category
                                    cannot be specified.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>categor=
y=3D&lt;Name of the category&gt;</code></pre>
                                 <p class=3D"p">This parameter specifies th=
e category into which the rules will be added. If a category is specified i=
t must exist or the
                                    request will fail. If a category is spe=
cified, a section cannot be specified.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>insertA=
fter=3D&lt;Index of rule&gt;</code></pre>
                                 <p class=3D"p">This parameter specifies th=
at the rules will be inserted after the specified rule index. If no section=
 or category is specified,
                                    the rules will be added to the section =
or category after the insertion point.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                 <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>insertB=
efore=3D&lt;Index of rule&gt;</code></pre>
                                 <p class=3D"p">This parameter specifies th=
at the rules will be inserted before the specified rule index.If no section=
 or category is specified,
                                    the rules will be added to the section =
or category before the insertion point. insertBefore takes precedence over =
insertAfter
                                    - if both are specified, the insertBefo=
re parameter will apply.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                           </ul>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">When a rule or group of rules are=
 inserted at an index which is part of either a section or a category, the =
category or section
                              parameter can be used along with index to spe=
cify the insertion location of the rule(s). If an index is given along with=
 a
                              section or category, but the index is not in =
that section or category, you will receive an error.=20
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">If no index is specified, rules w=
ill be inserted after the end of the access policy. If a category or sectio=
n is specified
                              but no index is specified, rules will be inse=
rted at the end of the category or section.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">In any given POST all of the rule=
s will be inserted at a single point. You cannot specify multiple insertion=
 locations in
                              a POST request.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"ol=
h_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                              <tbody><tr>
                                 <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=
=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/=
us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                    <section class=3D"note__content">
                                       <hr>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Rule order affects ho=
w orders are parsed by the <span class=3D"ph"><span class=3D"ph">management=
 center</span></span>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <hr>
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody></table></div>
                          =20
                        </section>
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic reference nested1" aria-labelledb=
y=3D"ariaid-title4" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title4">R=
esponse Structure</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body refbody">
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_zmj_lny_=
1cb__d9597e562">
                          =20
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"ol=
h_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                              <tbody><tr>
                                 <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=
=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/=
us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                    <section class=3D"note__content">
                                       <hr>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">The REST API will ser=
ve only 25 results per page. This can be increased up to 1000 using the lim=
it query parameter.</p>
                                      =20
                                       <hr>
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody></table></div>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">The response structure can be:</p=
>
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul" id=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb__ul=
_qnj_lny_1cb">
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">LOCATION =E2=80=93 Newly cr=
eated resource ID; for POST only=E2=80=94holds the new resource ID (as a UR=
I representation).</p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">CONTENT-TYPE =E2=80=93 Medi=
a type describing the response message body; describes the representation a=
nd syntax of the response message
                                    body.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Each response includes an H=
TTP status or error code. Available codes fall into these categories:</p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">20x - A two-hundred series =
code indicates successful operation, including:</p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>200 200</code></pre> =E2=80=93 "OK". Standard response for su=
ccessful requests.</section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>201 201</code></pre> =E2=80=93 "Created". Request completed; =
new resource
                                    created.</section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>202 202</code></pre> =E2=80=93 "Accepted". Request accepted, =
but processing not
                                    complete.</section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>204 204</code></pre> =E2=80=93 "No Content". Server successfu=
lly processed request;
                                    no content is being returned.</section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">4xx - A four-hundred series=
 code indicates a client-side error, including:</p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>400 400</code></pre> =E2=80=93"Bad Request".  Invalid query p=
arameters, including
                                    unrecognized parameters, missing parame=
ters, or invalid values.</section>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">This can indicate that the =
object was edited or
                                    deleted via REST API such that the corr=
esponding policy is invalidated.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>401 Invalid Session</code></pre> =E2=80=93 Invalid session.</=
section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>404 404</code></pre> =E2=80=93 "Not Found". The provided URL =
does not match an
                                    existing resource. For example, an HTTP=
 DELETE may fail because the resource is
                                    unavailable.</section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>405 405</code></pre> =E2=80=93 "Method Not Allowed". An HTTP =
request was presented
                                    that is not allowed on the resource; fo=
r example, a POST on a read-only resource.</section>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>422 422</code></pre> =E2=80=93 "Unprocessable Entity". The
                                    payload is too large. This will occur w=
hen you send a payload greater than 2048000
                                    bytes.</section>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">=E2=80=93 The payload conta=
ins an unprocessable or unreadable entity such as a invalid attribut name o=
r incorrect JSON syntax.</p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>429 Too Many Writes</code></pre> =E2=80=93 Parallel add/updat=
e/delete operations are
                                    blocked. Please retry the request.</sec=
tion>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre cod=
eblock"><code>429 429</code></pre> =E2=80=93 "Too Many Requests". Too many =
requests were sent to
                                    the API. This error will occur if you s=
end more than 120 requests per minute.</section>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">=E2=80=93 Too many concurre=
nt requests. The system cannot accept more than 10 parallel requests
                                    from all clients.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">=E2=80=93 Too many write op=
erations per server. The API will only allow one PUT, POST, or
                                    DELETE request per user on a server at =
a time.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">5xx - A five-hundred series=
 code indicates a server-side error.</p>
                                =20
                                =20
                              </li>
                           </ul>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">In the case of an error, in addit=
ion to the error code, the return response may include an error object cont=
aining more details
                              about the error. The JSON error/warning respo=
nse schema is as follows:
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"p">
                              <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code> {</code><=
/pre>
                              </section>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"p">
                              <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code> "error": =
{</code></pre>
                              </section>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"p">
                              <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code> "category=
": "FRAMEWORK",</code></pre>
                              </section>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"p">
                              <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code> "messages=
": [</code></pre>
                              </section>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"p">
                              <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code> {</code><=
/pre>
                              </section>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"p">
                              <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code> "descript=
ion": "Action is mandatory to be specified." </code></pre>
                              </section>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"p">
                              <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>}</code></=
pre>
                              </section>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"p">
                              <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code> ],</code>=
</pre>
                              </section>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"p">
                              <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>"severity"=
: "ERROR"</code></pre>
                              </section>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"p">
                              <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>}</code></=
pre>
                              </section>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"p">
                              <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>}</code></=
pre>
                              </section>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p"> where the object properties are:=
 </p>
                          =20
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table width=3D"10=
0%" border=3D"1" class=3D"table frame-all" id=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb__tab=
le_lyt_qmy_pv">
                              <caption><span class=3D"table--title-label ta=
bletitle">Table 1. </span><span class=3D"tabletitle">Object Properties</spa=
n></caption>
                              <colgroup>
                                 <col style=3D"width:33.33333333333333%">
                                 <col style=3D"width:33.33333333333333%">
                                 <col style=3D"width:33.33333333333333%">
                              </colgroup>
                              <thead class=3D"thead">
                                 <tr>
                                    <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"entry=
 colsep-1 rowsep-1" id=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb__table_lyt_qmy_pv__entry__1=
">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Property</p>
                                      =20
                                    </th>
                                    <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"entry=
 colsep-1 rowsep-1" id=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb__table_lyt_qmy_pv__entry__2=
">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Type</p>
                                      =20
                                    </th>
                                    <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"entry=
 colsep-1 rowsep-1" id=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb__table_lyt_qmy_pv__entry__3=
">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Description</p>
                                      =20
                                    </th>
                                 </tr>
                              </thead>
                              <tbody class=3D"tbody">
                                 <tr>
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb__table_lyt_qmy_pv__entry__1 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">messages</p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb__table_lyt_qmy_pv__entry__2 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">List of Dictionaries<=
/p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb__table_lyt_qmy_pv__entry__3 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">List of error or warn=
ing messages</p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr>
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb__table_lyt_qmy_pv__entry__1 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">code</p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb__table_lyt_qmy_pv__entry__2 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">String</p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb__table_lyt_qmy_pv__entry__3 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Error/Warning/Info co=
de</p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                 <tr>
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb__table_lyt_qmy_pv__entry__1 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">details</p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb__table_lyt_qmy_pv__entry__2 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">String</p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"reference_zmj_lny_1cb__table_lyt_qmy_pv__entry__3 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Detailed message corr=
esponding to Error/Warning/Info</p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>

                  <article class=3D"topic reference nested1" aria-labelledb=
y=3D"ariaid-title5" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"reference_xs5_ymy_1cb">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title5">R=
ate Limiting</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body refbody">
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_xs5_ymy_=
1cb__d9597e876">
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">The <span class=3D"ph"><span clas=
s=3D"ph">management center</span></span> REST API implements rate limiting =
to reduce network load.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">The API will accept no more than =
120 messages per minute from an individual IP address. It will only allow 1=
0 simultaneous
                              connections per IP address. These are not con=
figurable parameters.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">If a client exceeds these limits,=
 the API will give an HTTP 429 error.</p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic reference nested1" aria-labelledb=
y=3D"ariaid-title6" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"reference_cls_tmy_1cb">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title6">P=
ayload Limiting</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body refbody">
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_cls_tmy_=
1cb__d9597e913">
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">The API cannot accept a message w=
ith a payload greater than 2048000 bytes. This applies to both the REST API=
 and to API Explorer.
                              This is not a configurable parameter.
                           </p>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">If a message exceeds this limit, =
the API will give an HTTP 422 error.</p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic reference nested1" aria-labelledb=
y=3D"ariaid-title7" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"reference_frz_mmy_1cb">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title7">O=
bject Overrides</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body refbody">
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"reference_frz_mmy_=
1cb__section_wc4_4ll_wy">
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">An override defines an alternate =
value for an object, which the system uses for the device or domain specifi=
ed. In a single
                              request user can create multiple overrides fo=
r multiple objects using bulk operation.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">When an object is overriden, the =
alternate values will be provided for that object when it is requested. Thi=
s does not overwrite
                              the original values, which will return if the=
 override is removed. The override gives alternate values for all fields in=
 the
                              object except for the <code class=3D"ph codep=
h">Name</code> and <code class=3D"ph codeph">Description</code> fields.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">The URL for this feature is:</p>
                           <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>https://:{fmc=
_ip_or_name}:{https_port}/api/fmc_config/v1/domain/{Domain_uuid} /object/ho=
sts</code></pre>
                           <p class=3D"p">Request payload to create an over=
ride for object =E2=80=9Ctesthost=E2=80=9D on domain =E2=80=9C"Global \\ RE=
TAIL" with the override value being "1.2.3.5":</p>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"p">
                              <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><code>{
  "type": "Host",
  "value": "1.2.3.5",
  "overrides": {
    "parent": {
      "id": &lt;Parent UUID&gt;
      "type": "Host"
    },
    "target": {
      "name": "Global \\ RETAIL",
      "id": &lt;target domain UUID&gt;,
      "type": "Domain"
    }
  },
  "overridable": true,
  "description": " ",
  "name": "testhost",
}
</code></pre>
                              </section>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Optional:</p>
                          =20
                           <section class=3D"p"><pre class=3D"pre codeblock=
"><code>?bulk=3Dtrue</code></pre> indicates the override creation for more =
than one object.</section>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">GET:</p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">URL to list all overrides on a pa=
rticular object: <code class=3D"ph codeph">/api/fmc_config/v1/domain/{domai=
n_UUID}/object/hosts/{host_UUID}/overrides</code></p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">URL for override for an object on=
 a particular domain or device: <code class=3D"ph codeph">/api/fmc_config/v=
1/domain/{domain_UUID}/object/hosts/{host_UUID}?overrideTargetId=3D{target_=
UUID}</code></p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">URL for all the overrides on a pa=
rticular domain or device: <code class=3D"ph codeph">/api/fmc_config/v1/dom=
ain/{domain_UUID}/object/hosts?overrideTargetId=3D{target_UUID}</code></p>
                          =20
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"ol=
h_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                              <tbody><tr>
                                 <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" role=
=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/=
us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                    <section class=3D"note__content">
                                       <hr>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">When overridden, the =
parent object value will never change.</p>
                                      =20
                                       <hr>
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody></table></div>
                          =20
                        </section>
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></nav=
>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                  </article>

eration responds within 60

u perform

st 120 seconds

s initiated. The
                                          response of the POST operation in=
cludes a task

tatus. You can
                                          monitor the completion of the tas=
k by performing a
                                          GET operation on the task object =
with its task ID.
                                          For more information, see <a clas=
s=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower=

                              <p class=3D"p">Request Type: <span class=3D"k=
eyword cmdname">GET</span></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Description: Retrieves the Any=
Connect Custom Attribute associated with the specified
                                 ID. If no ID is specified for a GET, retri=
eves list of all AnyConnect Custom
                                 Attribute objects.
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">URL for listing:
                                 <code class=3D"ph codeph">/api/fmc_config/=
v1/domain/{domainUUID}/object/anyconnectcustomattributes</code></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">URL for GET by ID:
                                 <code class=3D"ph codeph">/api/fmc_config/=
v1/domain/{domainUUID}/object/anyconnectcustomattributes/{objectId}</code><=
/p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">URL to list all overrides: <co=
de class=3D"ph codeph"></code></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p"><code class=3D"ph codeph">/api=
/fmc_config/v1/domain/{domainUUID}/object/anyconnectcustomattributes/{conta=
inerUUID}/override</code></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Permissions: Object Manager</p=
>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Parameters available for filte=
ring: To be used in conjunction with
                                 <code class=3D"ph codeph">"unusedOnly:true=
"</code> to search for unused objects and
                                 <code class=3D"ph codeph">"nameOrValue:{na=
meOrValue}"</code> to search for both name and
                                 value
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                          =20

                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title8=
69">POST upgradepackage</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body refbody">
                           <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_76103__d9597=
e49411">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Request Type: <span class=3D"k=
eyword cmdname">POST</span></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Description: Dependent on the =
parameters, this POST operation either pushes available software upgrade pa=
ckages to applicable
                                 devices running <span class=3D"ph"><span c=
lass=3D"ph">threat
                                       											defense</span></span> or =
initiates the upgrade process for applicable devices running <span class=3D=
"ph"><span class=3D"ph">threat
                                       											defense</span></span>. Th=
is process is applicable for standalone, clustered, or high availability pa=
irs with the following limitations:
                              </p>
                             =20
                              <ul class=3D"ul">
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">For all configurations, =
ensure that the current POST operation is completed successfully before pro=
ceeding to the next POST
                                       operation.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Perform the POST operati=
on on the primary node of a high availability pair. Do not perform the POST=
 operation for more than
                                       one high availability pair at a time=
.=20
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                                 <li class=3D"li">
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Perform the POST operati=
on on the </p>
                                   =20
                                 </li>
                              </ul>
                             =20
                              <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D=
"olh_note" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">
                                 <tbody><tr>
                                    <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" rol=
e=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en=
/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                       <section class=3D"note__content">
                                          <hr> Typically, the first POST op=
eration responds within 60 seconds. Cisco
                                          recommends that you perform subse=
quent POST operations at least 120
                                          seconds after the first POST oper=
ation was initiated. The response
                                          of the POST operation includes a =
task object, with a task ID and
                                          task status. You can monitor the =
completion of the task by
                                          performing a GET operation on the=
 task object with its task ID. For
                                          more information, see <a class=3D=
"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/741=
/api/REST/secure_firewall_management_center_rest_api_quick_start_guide_741/=
Objects_In_The_REST_API.html#reference_bl4_kpy_1cb">GET taskstatuses</a>.
                                          <hr>
                                       </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                              </tbody></table></div>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">URL:<code class=3D"ph codeph">=
/api/fmc_platform/v1/updates/upgrades/</code></p>
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">Permissions:
                                 System &gt; Tools &gt; Scheduling
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->

gle-gray-100); }

ore { background: var(--google-blue-300); }
